Metabolomics: from study design to data analysis in R

Online, 1-4 November

Course website: [ https://www.physalia-courses.org/courses-workshops/course55/ ]( https://www.physalia-courses.org/courses-workshops/course55/ ) 
 


Instructor: Dr. Pietro Franceschi (Fondazione E. Mach, Italy)



OVERVIEW: The aim of the course is to cover some of the fundamental aspects of metabolomics from the ?data analyst? point of view. We will  cover all the key aspects which have to be considered to set-up a successful metabolomics investigation, from the practical issues related to study/analytical design to data pre-processing and statistical analysis. The course will be delivered relying on a mixture of lectures, computer-based practical sections, and group discussions.
 




Prerequisites: Familiarity with R will be assumed. A full day of the course will be however devoted to a fast introduction to data carpentry and visualization in R. A basic experience in metabolomics will be welcomed.



